
"Gordie you okay?" Chris asked the boy, who had started fidgeting.
"Yeah," came the response. Then Gordie slowly, shakily, sat up. Once his eyes landed on me, the corners of his lips quirked up, but just slightly. Then looking down at himself, he flushed.
I laughed slightly, then got up, and walked away to give the boys some privacy.
* * * * * *Overall, this was my favorite scene to write.